The paper deals with the application of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for medical image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of adversarial networks and image-to-image translation techniques also suggests a focus on generative models (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific application of the proposed method to knee MR image datasets suggests a possible fit with multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
